'''''Operation Sabotage''''' is a [[interactive fiction|text adventure]] game by Ray Sato for the [[TRS-80]] and published by ''[[SoftSide|SoftSide Magazine]]'' in 1982. It was ported by Rich Bouchard to the [[Atari 8-bit computers]] and translated for [[Apple II]] by Ron Shaker<ref>{{Cite magazine |year=1982 |title=Operation: Sabotage by Ray Sato |url=https://archive.org/details/softside-magazine-47/page/n29 |magazine=SoftSide |volume=5 |issue=11 |page=29}}</ref> and later the [[IBM Personal Computer]] by Fred Condo & Kerry Shetline.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Condo |first=Fred |last2=Shetline |first2=Kerry |year=1983 |title=Operation: Sabotage by Ray Sato |url=https://archive.org/details/softside-magazine-51/page/n42 |magazine=SoftSide |volume=6 |issue=3 |page=40}}</ref>  The game was republished in ''The Best of SoftSide'' (1983), which also included the program on an accompanying [[floppy disk|5Â¼-inch floppy disk]].<ref name="bss">{{Cite book |title=The Best of SoftSide |publisher=SoftSide Publications, Inc. |year=1983 |editor-last=Condo |editor-first=Fred |location=Milford, New Hampshire |chapter=Operation Sabotage}}</ref>

